# Init And Reset

Use this reference for repository setup, reinitialization, and the interactive global CLI Skill prompt.

## `skills-seed init`

Purpose:

- Create `.skills-seed/config.yaml`.
- Create `.skills-seed/context/` seed files.
- Configure project mode or workspace mode.
- Configure the AI execution agent and generated Skill target.
- In interactive mode, optionally install/update the global `skills-seed-cli` operation Skill only when the detected environment is missing it or has stale metadata.

Flags:

- `--locale, -l`: CLI UI, config-template, and seed-context language.
- `--skills-locale`: generated Skill and learned natural-language content language.
- `--mode`: `project` or `workspace`.
- `--agent`: AI execution engine, usually `claude` or `codex`.
- `--skills`: generated Skill provider/layout, usually `claude` or `codex`.
- `--workspace`: shortcut for `--mode workspace`.
- `--no-interactive`: skip prompts.

Use cases:

- Interactive first setup: `skills-seed init`
- Project setup for Codex: `skills-seed init --mode project --agent codex --skills codex --locale zh-CN --skills-locale en-US --no-interactive`
- Workspace setup: `skills-seed init --workspace --agent claude --skills claude --locale zh-CN --no-interactive`

Interactive global CLI Skill behavior:

- `init` auto-detects available Claude/Codex global environments.
- It checks whether the generated global CLI Skill is missing or outdated for the current `skills-seed` binary.
- Only then does it ask install/update versus skip.
- It does not ask which agent target to install. Use `skills-seed cli-skills install --target ...` for manual target control.

Boundaries:

- `init` does not learn project conventions. Run `skills-seed sync` after setup.
- `init` does not delete generated project Skills.
- `init` does not uninstall global CLI Skills.

## `skills-seed reset`

Purpose:

- Back up existing `.skills-seed` under `.skills-seed.backup/<timestamp>`.
- Recreate local skills-seed state with selected project/workspace settings.

Flags:

- `--locale, -l`: CLI UI/config/seed context language.
- `--skills-locale`: generated Skill and learned natural-language content language.
- `--mode`: `project` or `workspace`.
- `--workspace`: shortcut for `--mode workspace`.

Use cases:

- Recreate project state: `skills-seed reset --mode project --locale zh-CN`
- Convert to workspace mode: `skills-seed reset --workspace --locale zh-CN`

Use reset when:

- The local `.skills-seed` state is inconsistent.
- You need to switch between project and workspace mode.
- You want to recreate default config/context files while keeping a backup.

Avoid reset when:

- You only need to update generated Skills: use `skills-seed generate skills`.
- You only need to learn current code: use `skills-seed sync` or `skills-seed learn current`.
- You only need to update the global CLI Skill: use `skills-seed cli-skills install`.
